goals.question: What is the overall trend of GitHub activity over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of count over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the general trend of GitHub activity over the recorded time period.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the count of events?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the spread of the count of events and help identify any outliers or patterns.

goals.question: What is the average count of events per day?
goals.visualization: bar chart of average count per day
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the average number of events per day and help identify any days with particularly high or low activity.

goals.question: What is the correlation between time and count?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of count over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the relationship between time and count and help identify any patterns or trends.

goals.question: What is the distribution of GitHub activity by hour of the day?
goals.visualization: bar chart of count by hour
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the distribution of GitHub activity by hour of the day and help identify any peak hours of activity.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of GitHub activity over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['GitHub Activity'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Count of Events')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the count of events?')
    plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.75)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['day'] = data['time'].dt.date
    daily_average = data.groupby('day')['count'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.bar(daily_average['day'], daily_average['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Average Count of Events')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average count of events per day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    hourly_counts = data.groupby('hour')['count'].sum()
    
    plt.bar(hourly_counts.index, hourly_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Hour of the Day')
    plt.ylabel('Total Events')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of GitHub activity by hour of the day?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(range(0, 24))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
